
[1]inheritable

   INHER'ITABLE, a. That may be inherited; transmissible or descendible
   from the ancestor to the heir by course of law; as an inheritable
   estate or title.

   1. That may be transmitted from the parent to the child; as inheritable
   qualities or infirmities.

   2. Capable of taking by inheritance, or of receiving by descent.

   By attainder--the blood of the person attainted is so corrupted as to
   be rendered no longer inheritable.
